Now that you have picked a few interests and potential career goals, and discovered which
            courses and opportunities match, it's time to design your degree plan. The degree plan specifies which
            courses and opportunities you'll take each semester until you graduate. RadGrad is designed to help you
            graduate as quickly and efficiently as possible, with the best possible preparation for life after the
            diploma.

In addition to recommending courses and opportunities, RadGrad also provides warnings when
            things don't look right. For example, RadGrad tells you when you add a course to a semester without
            having taken the prerequisite, or if your degree plan doesn't include all of the required courses.

In the current competitive job market, just getting a degree isn't enough to
            guarantee great job opportunities. RadGrad provides a new metric called

to help you develop the
            complete package of skills and experiences.
